1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
Welcome to Executable Talk — a VS Code
extension that turns Markdown
presentations into interactive demos with
live code execution.

2
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:15,500
Executable Talk lets you open files
directly from your slides.

3
00:00:24,900 --> 00:00:28,100
Let's open package.json to see the project
configuration.

4
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:30,600
And here's the README with the project
documentation.

5
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:35,900
You can highlight specific lines in a
file. Great for drawing attention to key
code.

6
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:50,100
Highlight a range of lines — lines one
through ten.

7
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:51,800
Or highlight a single line — line twenty.

8
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:55,500
Terminal commands run directly from your
slides. They require Workspace Trust.

9
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:03,500
Check the installed npm version.

10
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,600
List the files in the project directory.

11
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:16,500
Sequences let you chain multiple actions
together — open a file and highlight
specific lines in one click.

12
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:31,600
You can embed live file content directly
in your slides. This always shows the
current version of the file.

13
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:45,000
Command output rendering executes a
command and embeds the result right in the
slide. Useful for showing versions or
directory listings.

14
00:01:52,500 --> 00:01:58,500
Diff rendering shows git changes inline.
You can compare any file against a
previous commit.

15
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:07,500
Any VS Code command can be triggered from
a slide.

16
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:20,300
Open the VS Code settings panel.

17
00:02:20,300 --> 00:02:22,800
Toggle the sidebar visibility.

18
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,600
Search for markdown extensions in the
marketplace.

19
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:35,300
New in version 0.2 — YAML action blocks.
Instead of URL-encoded links, you can
write actions as readable YAML. Both
formats work side by side.

20
00:02:53,800 --> 00:03:01,000
YAML blocks make complex actions much
easier to read. Here we highlight lines in
the extension entry point.

21
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Sequences are dramatically cleaner in
YAML. This one opens a file, highlights
key lines, and runs a terminal command —
all in a single block.

22
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:30,900
Terminal and VS Code commands in YAML are
just as clean.

23
00:03:30,900 --> 00:03:33,400
Run an echo command from YAML.

24
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:39,800
Toggle the sidebar with a single YAML
block.

25
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:46,000
Preflight validation catches errors before
you present. The validator checks for:

26
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,500
Missing files in your action links.

27
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:56,000
Out-of-range line numbers in highlight
actions.

28
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,500
Missing debug configurations.

29
00:03:58,500 --> 00:04:01,000
Unavailable terminal commands on your
platform.

30
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,200
Trust issues when running in an untrusted
workspace.

31
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:08,600
These action blocks have intentional
errors. The validator will catch them.

32
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:14,700
This file doesn't exist — the validator
flags it.

33
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:21,100
These line numbers are way out of range.

34
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:27,800
When actions fail during a presentation,
you see a toast notification.

35
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:33,900
File open errors show which file couldn't
be found.

36
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:37,500
Highlight errors show which lines are out
of range.

37
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:40,000
Terminal errors show the failing command.

38
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,500
Sequence errors show a step-by-step
breakdown.

39
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:46,500
Toasts auto-dismiss after eight seconds.
Hover to pause the timer.

40
00:04:46,500 --> 00:04:50,100
When editing deck files you get full IDE
support.

41
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:56,200
Autocomplete suggests action types and
parameters as you type.

42
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:59,000
Hover docs show descriptions and parameter
tables.

43
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,800
Real-time diagnostics show red squiggles
for errors.

44
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:06,600
Try it yourself — open this file and edit
an action block.

45
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:15,000
That's the end of the demo. Press Escape
to exit, or Ctrl+Z to undo any IDE changes
made during the presentation.
